The paper presents a novel hierarchical predictor-corrector scheme for learning to understand and control complex nonlinear physical systems over long time frames. The approach involves training end-to-end using a differentiable PDE solver. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
